Bayes Therom takes new information as it becomes available in order to create new optimal outcomes.Bayes Therom uses posterior probability which uses evolutionary solver in order to take previous information and turn it into conditional future results based on the previous infromation. 

We need posterior probabilities in order to make better future decisions and learn from the past. A specific example in which we did this is when we took the results of advertising in a test market and then used that information to decide whether to advertise in a national market.
